Spotfinder is an application that uses Facebook information in order 
to predict user preferences.

1. A Facebook application is created to get information and rating of 
users and other social information about the users.

2. A finder program with ab innovative comparing algorithm uses social
information to deduce relationship strength. Then Spotfinder can proposed 
places that have greater change of the user linking it based on friends' 
ratings and relationship strength.

This project is written by Kervin Ramen as part of his MSc project at 
the University of Mauritius.

